The South African Airways is releasing the annual financial results. This comes after the chairperson of the Parliament’s Standing Committee on Finance Yunus Carrim said it’s an indictment on both the ruling party and government that SAA’s finances have deteriorated to the level that they are at. Carrim blames government for the demise of the airline under former board chairperson Dudu Myeni.  About SABC View all posts by SABC